<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="66.[180,1071,937,1260]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
Distribution (
<figureCitation box="[367,437,1161,1185]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="66.[181,210,680,698]" captionTargetBox="[181,1065,113,643]" captionTargetId="figure-256@66.[181,1065,113,643]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="Fig. 35. Distribution of Lindholmiola gyria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5842370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5842370/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Fig 35</figureCitation>
): This species is only known from a small coastal stripe in the south-western part of the vilayet 
<collectingRegion box="[632,722,1198,1222]" country="Turkey" name="Antalya" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Antalya</collectingRegion>
. The distribution range covers the Island Kekova (= E of Kaş) and the surroundings of Kemer to Phaselis.
</paragraph>
